        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:26PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Riverton, or near Springfield, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield, Chatham, Sherman, Rochester, Riverton, Williamsville,
Mechanicsburg, Dawson, Buffalo, Illinois State Fairgrounds, Abraham
Lincoln Capital Airport, Jerome, Southern View, Leland Grove,
Grandview, Spaulding, Clear Lake, and Glenarm.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 55 between mile markers 85 and 111.
Interstate 72 between mile markers 95 and 120.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
